reground at first, looking toward him from the floor.\n\nA close view shows a large card or game board held by white-gloved cartoon hands. The front reads “REXALL 1¢ SALE,” with a huge numeral “1” in the center and the word “SALE” below. A page is turned over, leaving a blank white surface. A red crayon or marker appears in a gloved hand and begins drawing on the page. A product picture materializes on the left: an orange box labeled “REXALL BUFFERED ASPIRIN.” Black price lettering appears to the right, including “REG.” and “98¢.” A copper-colored penny marked “1¢” is then placed near the regular price, visually showing the added penny. The display changes to two orange Rexall Buffered Aspirin boxes side by side, with large black “99¢” text beside them, showing the two-for-a-penny-more offer.\n\nThe girl, still in her pink dress, is shown again in Rexall Land, now propped on one hand and watching with a curious expression. Behind her, red signs with white lettering advertise the “1¢ SALE,” and a small table holds another pyramid of white packages. The rabbit returns to center stage among the displays. He presents a blue and white box labeled “Panovite” or Panavite, identified by the sale context as Rexall multiple vitamins. The package stands upright beside him, large enough to be read clearly, with “MULTIPLE VITAMINS” visible on the front. The rabbit gestures toward it proudly, then hops or spins away in a burst of motion. The product remains on a clean graphic background while large black text appears: “REG. $2.98.” The display then changes to two blue vitamin packages, with “NOW,” a penny symbol, and “$2.98” arranged to communicate the one-cent-added sale price.\n\nNext, a hand lotion product is presented against a warm yellow background. A pale bottle with a red cap stands upright, its label showing dark lettering and a dark decorative mark near the lower front. Large black text to the left reads “REG. 98¢.” The single bottle becomes two matching bottles side by side, again using the same visual formula of doubling the product for the one-cent sale offer. The girl reappears smiling slightly and looking off toward the rabbit and the signs, seeming more delighted and reassured than when she first arrived.\n\nThe rabbit stands once more in the Rexall Land setting, surrounded by the same Rexall towers, sale banners, and neatly stacked product displays. He gestures broadly as if concluding the demonstration. Then his body transforms into a large white numeral “1,” with his red nose and face incorporated into the top portion, and small arms stretched outward. The fantasy store background fades behind him, leaving the animated number “1” centered on a pale blue background. The final sale graphic forms around it: “REXALL” on the left, a large white “1” with a cent sign beside it in the middle, and “SALE” on the right. This graphic slides aside to reveal the Rexall store sign: an orange, rounded rectangular logo with the word “Rexall” in white script outlined in dark lettering, set against a warm yellow background.",
